This paper is about dialogue systems, which are commonly studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a novel approach to multi-domain dialogue generation, which involves training teacher models in individual domains and transferring their knowledge to a universal student model. This approach involves machine learning techniques such as policy learning and knowledge transfer, which are also relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of using state trackers in dialogue systems, which is a topic of interest in the field of software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the proposed approach involves training models using labeled data, which is a common theme in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
